Add `PackageScope` type and extend `InstalledPackage` in both the server-side scanner and the shared client-facing schema.

## Server-side (`apps/server/src/services/marketplace/installed-scanner.ts`)

Update the `InstalledPackage` interface at line 24:

```typescript
/** Scope origin of an installed package. */
export type PackageScope = 'global' | 'agent-local' | 'override';

export interface InstalledPackage {
  /** Package name from `.dork/manifest.json`. */
  name: string;
  /** Package version from `.dork/manifest.json`. */
  version: string;
  /** Package type (plugin, agent, skill-pack, adapter). */
  type: PackageType;
  /** Absolute path to the package root directory. */
  installPath: string;
  /** Marketplace source the package was installed from, if known. */
  installedFrom?: string;
  /** ISO timestamp when the package was installed, if known. */
  installedAt?: string;
  /** Scope origin — undefined means global (backward compat when no projectPath passed). */
  scope?: PackageScope;
  /** Agent project path — set only for agent-local and override packages. */
  agentPath?: string;
}
```

## Shared client schema (`packages/shared/src/marketplace-schemas.ts`)

Update the `InstalledPackage` interface (around line 283) and add the `PackageScope` type:

```typescript
/**
 * Scope origin of an installed package.
 *
 * - `'global'` — installed at `${dorkHome}/plugins/` or `${dorkHome}/agents/`
 * - `'agent-local'` — installed at `${agent.projectPath}/.dork/plugins/`
 * - `'override'` — agent-local package that shadows a global with the same name
 */
export type PackageScope = 'global' | 'agent-local' | 'override';

export interface InstalledPackage {
  name: string;
  version: string;
  type: MarketplacePackageType;
  installPath: string;
  installedFrom?: string;
  installedAt?: string;
  /** Scope origin — undefined means global (backward compat). */
  scope?: PackageScope;
  /** Agent project path — set for agent-local and override packages. */
  agentPath?: string;
}
```

