Enhance the `ConflictDetector` in `apps/server/src/services/marketplace/conflict-detector.ts` to emit a warning-level conflict when installing a package agent-locally and a global package with the same name already exists.

## Current behavior

The `#detectPackageNameConflict` method (line 120) checks whether a package with the same name exists at the `scopeRoot` (which is `ctx.projectPath ?? this.#dorkHome`). When `projectPath` is set, it only checks the agent-local scope — it does NOT cross-check against global.

## Required change

After the existing package-name conflict detection, add a cross-scope warning check. When `ctx.projectPath` is provided and the package name does NOT conflict at the agent-local scope (that case is already an error), check whether a global package with the same name exists. If so, emit a warning.

Modify the `#detectPackageNameConflict` method:

```typescript
async #detectPackageNameConflict(
  ctx: ConflictDetectionContext,
  scopeRoot: string
): Promise<ConflictReport[]> {
  const candidates = [
    join(scopeRoot, 'plugins', ctx.manifest.name),
    join(scopeRoot, 'agents', ctx.manifest.name),
  ];
  for (const candidate of candidates) {
    if (await pathExists(candidate)) {
      return [
        {
          level: 'error',
          type: 'package-name',
          description: `A package named "${ctx.manifest.name}" is already installed at this scope.`,
          conflictingPackage: ctx.manifest.name,
        },
      ];
    }
  }

  // Cross-scope warning: installing agent-locally when a global version exists.
  // This is informational only — the install proceeds and the local version
  // will override the global one for this agent.
  if (ctx.projectPath) {
    const globalCandidates = [
      join(this.#dorkHome, 'plugins', ctx.manifest.name),
      join(this.#dorkHome, 'agents', ctx.manifest.name),
    ];
    for (const globalCandidate of globalCandidates) {
      if (await pathExists(globalCandidate)) {
        return [
          {
            level: 'warning',
            type: 'package-name',
            description: `Package "${ctx.manifest.name}" is installed globally. The agent-local version will override it for this agent.`,
            conflictingPackage: ctx.manifest.name,
          },
        ];
      }
    }
  }

  return [];
}
```

## Acceptance Criteria

- Installing a package agent-locally when the same name exists globally returns a warning (not error)
- Warning description mentions the override behavior
- No warning when the names do not collide globally
- Existing error behavior for same-scope name collision is unchanged
- Warning level allows the install to proceed (not blocking)

## Tests

Add to `apps/server/src/services/marketplace/__tests__/conflict-detector.test.ts`:

